> Maybe at GTE.  The market is *crying* for large memory support on i386.
If the market wants to see it in the official kernel, it should send us a
patch that does it cleanly. If the market has any sense, it'll quickly
realize that it can't be done cleanly, at which point the market will
decide to invest in a nice 64-bit machine.
